n</strong> and <strong>Zelensky</strong> aren=E2=80=99t in the same room an=
d Trump has called the latter a dictator. =E2=80=9CDo I think that presenti=
ng a proposal to take half [of Ukraine=E2=80=99s] minerals, at this stage o=
f the game, is not very smart?=E2=80=9D the exec said. =E2=80=9CYes. Is it =
part of a plan to pressure [Zelensky] to reach an agreement? Yes.
Do you have to show Putin a path to his defeat? Yes, you have to make a cre=
dible threat to Putin that if you don=E2=80=99t agree to a deal, we=E2=80=
=99re going to fucking ramp up the aid, and you could lose this thing.=E2=
=80=9D (Alas, the administration seems to have skipped over that last part.=
) He said a negotiated solution is the only way out of the war. =E2=80=9CIt=
=E2=80=99s a stalemate, despite the fact that we=E2=80=99re arming them to =
