ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">As I continued my canvassing of Wall Street, I was intrigued by some re=
cent comments
offered by <strong>Richard Haass</strong>, the former president of the Coun=
cil on Foreign Relations (of which I=E2=80=99m a member) and former Lazard =
board member who is now a senior counselor at Centerview Partners, the imme=
nsely successful advisory boutique founded by <strong>Blair Effron </strong=
>and <strong>Robert Pruzan</strong>. Richard is one of the few Wall Streete=
rs willing to speak up under his own name. In a Substack <a href=3D"https:/=
/email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dWSVBueDZ3c2=
00Y3NQcFdpYnRkND0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9yaWNoYXJkaGFhc3Muc3Vic3RhY2suY29tL=
z91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODIlMkYxOSUyRjI1JTI5=
XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9RHJ5K1Bvd2RlcistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODIlMkYxNiUyRjI=
